# Scope Control (MANDATORY)

## Only Do What the Ticket Asks

- Read the primer doc for the current ticket BEFORE writing any code
- Implement ONLY the deliverables listed in the primer's checklist
- If the ticket says "modify file X", only modify file X
- If the ticket says "add tests for Y", only add tests for Y

## Do NOT

- Refactor code that isn't part of the current ticket
- Add docstrings, type hints, or comments to code you didn't write or change
- Rename variables or functions outside your ticket scope
- "Clean up" imports, formatting, or structure in unrelated files
- Add features, utilities, or helpers not specified in the ticket
- Modify configuration files unless the ticket explicitly requires it
- Add packages to requirements.txt unless the ticket explicitly requires it
- Import modules from tickets that haven't been implemented yet

## When You Find Issues Outside Your Scope

- Do NOT fix bugs in other modules
- Do NOT refactor code that "could be better"
- Note the issue in your commit message or PR description
- Let the reviewer decide whether to create a follow-up ticket

## File Protection

- Check the primer's "Files You Should NOT Modify" section before editing anything
- If a file is not listed in "Files to Modify", do not touch it
- Never modify completed ticket modules unless the current ticket explicitly requires it
